SIMPLE: feasible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feasible
<hw>Fea"si*ble</hw> <pr>(f⟦emac⟧"z⟦icr⟧*b'l)</pr> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>faisable</ets>, fr. <ets>faire</ets> to make or do, fr. L.
<ets>facere</ets>. See <er>Fact</er>, <er>Feat</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being done, executed, or effected;
practicable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Always existing before their eyes as a thing <qex>feasible</qex>
in practice.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was not <qex>feasible</qex> to gratify so many ambitions.</q>
<rj><qau>Beaconsfield.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fit to be used or tilled, as land.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>R. Trumbull.</au></rj></p>

<p><wordforms><wf>Fea"si*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
--<wf>Fea"si*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feast</ent>⟦br⟧
